# =============================================================================
# MasterBrain — .gitignore
#
# Model: the GitHub repo carries CODE + SCAFFOLDING + TEMPLATES + DOCS + the
# safe architecture SEED pages only. REAL brain/vault content (canonical pages,
# entities, components, queries, comparisons, notes, sources, structured memory)
# lives ONLY on the Unraid /data volume and is restored from backup — it is
# IGNORED BY DEFAULT here so it can never be committed by accident.
# Folder structure is preserved via .gitkeep placeholders and area READMEs.
# Use a PRIVATE repository.
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets / local config -------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Python caches / build --------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- OS / editor / vault cruft ----------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
.obsidian/
.cache/
*.tmp
*.log

# --- Durable structured memory (lives on /data, not git) --------------------
graph-memory/*.jsonl

# --- Generated graph output (regenerable cache) -----------------------------
graphify-out/

# --- Private knowledge: raw sources -----------------------------------------
raw/**
!raw/**/
!raw/README.md

# --- Private knowledge: agent inbox notes -----------------------------------
inbox/**
!inbox/**/
!inbox/README.md

# --- Private knowledge: per-agent notes (keep registry only) ----------------
agents/*/**
!agents/**/
!agents/agent-registry.md

# =============================================================================
# CANONICAL VAULT CONTENT — ignore by default; allowlist only safe seeds.
# Future real pages dropped into these folders are IGNORED automatically.
# To publish a specific page later, add an explicit `!path/to/file.md` line.
# =============================================================================

# concepts/ — only the architecture seed is tracked
concepts/**
!concepts/**/
!concepts/shared-external-agent-memory-graph.md

# projects/ — only the second-brain build/architecture docs are tracked
projects/**
!projects/**/
!projects/second-brain/*.md

# entities/ components/ queries/ comparisons/ — scaffold only (no seed docs)
entities/**
!entities/**/

components/**
!components/**/

queries/**
!queries/**/
# The generated review queue embeds private claim text — never track it, even
# if queries/ is ever selectively un-ignored (PROCESS.md rule 14).
queries/review-queue.md

comparisons/**
!comparisons/**/

# --- Always keep folder placeholders + area READMEs so structure survives ---
!**/.gitkeep
!**/README.md
